This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) because it proposes a new approach that combines Reinforcement Learning and Model Predictive Control using scalable approximate inference. It also presents two variations of the algorithm based on the Sparse Spectrum Gaussian Process model, which is a popular machine learning technique. 

It is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics) because the paper discusses the need for robotic systems to make decisions quickly and robustly in uncertain and dynamic environments. The proposed approach is aimed at improving the performance of robotic systems in such environments. 

The paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because it proposes a new approach that combines two popular AI techniques, Reinforcement Learning and Model Predictive Control. 

It may belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control) because it discusses the need for control policies in robotic systems and proposes a new approach for computing optimal control policies. 

Finally, it may belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) because the proposed approach could potentially be used in computer vision applications that require decision-making in uncertain and dynamic environments.
